            <p>Synagogue Chambers<lb/>
                Septr 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. 5618<lb/>
                Revd S. Morais<lb/>
                Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>It affords me<lb/> great pleasure to communicate<lb/> to you that at the Stated<lb/> Meeting of the Congregation Mr. &#34;I.&#34;<lb/> held on Sunday last&#44; you were<lb/> re&#45;elected Hazan of the Congregation<lb/> for a further term of Five Years<lb/> from the expiration of your present<lb/> engagement. &#40;next Passover&#41;. and<lb/> at an increased salary&#44; say<lb/> &#40;&#36;2000&#41; Two Thousand Dollars<lb/> per Annum commencing at that<lb/> time&#44; and with my best wishes<lb/> for your continued health as well as<lb/> that of your Family&#44; and that you<lb/> may see the congregation prosper as<lb/> you desire&#44; <del>it&#44;</del> I am Revd Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>yours very Truly<lb/>
                A. Hart<lb/>
                Parnass &#34;KKM&#34;<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
    </text>
